<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏃 RB001 Week 8 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Ship It — Publish &amp; Present · <strong>Course:</strong> Obby Architect · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>This week you <strong>ship</strong> your obby. In Roblox Studio: <strong>File → Publish to Roblox</strong>, give your game a real name and description, set it to <strong>Public</strong> in Game Settings → Permissions, and add a game icon. Then you present it.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>This week you read <strong>your own</strong> code. Open your favorite script in your game — the one you are most proud of.</p>
<p><strong>Copy your favorite script here (or the most important part of it):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What does this script do? Walk through it line by line in your own words.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Predict: if you deleted this script and pressed Play, what would break first in your game?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each launch checklist below has a problem. Read what the student <strong>wanted</strong>, find what went wrong, then write the fix and explain it.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — Mina published her obby and sent the link to her friend. Her friend sees "This experience is unavailable" and cannot play.</p>
<pre><code>Game name:    Mina's Mega Obby
Description:  Jump through 5 worlds of lava and vanishing bridges!
Published:    yes
Public:       OFF (Private)
Game icon:    uploaded
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fix:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — Junho's game is public, but nobody who finds it knows what it is or wants to click it.</p>
<pre><code>Game name:    Untitled Game
Description:  (empty)
Published:    yes
Public:       ON
Game icon:    default gray icon
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fix:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Sora published her game on Monday. On Tuesday she built a whole new lava section in Studio. Her friend plays the game online — but the new section is <strong>not there</strong>.</p>
<pre><code>Game name:    Sora's Sky Run
Description:  Climb to the clouds. Don't touch the lava!
Published:    yes — on Monday
New section:  built Tuesday, saved in Studio only
Public:       ON
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> changes in Studio only go online when you do one thing again.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fix:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now publish your obby: <strong>File → Publish to Roblox</strong>, write a real name and a 1–2 sentence description, turn on <strong>Public</strong>, and add an icon. Open your game's page on the Roblox website. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your game's public page, then tell the story of your game. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My game is called … and in it you …</p>
<p>The hardest bug I fixed was …</p>
<p>I fixed it by …</p>
<p>My favorite script is … because it …</p>
<p>If I kept building, the next thing I would add is …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>This is your <strong>presentation video</strong>. Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) and present your published game like a real developer. Try to use these words: <strong>publish</strong>, <strong>public</strong>, <strong>description</strong>, <strong>bug</strong>, <strong>script</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your game's page on the Roblox website and say its name and what kind of game it is.</li>
<li>Play through one full section of your obby.</li>
<li>Open your favorite script and say what it does.</li>
<li>Tell the hardest bug you fixed in this course and how you fixed it.</li>
<li>Say what you would build next.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Use the space below to plan it before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
